    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains three numerical dimensions (X, Y, Z) with 16 synthetic observations across two clusters. Synthetic data was generated using normal distributions (Cluster Alpha: \u03bc=2, \u03c3=0.3; Cluster Beta: \u03bc=8, \u03c3=0.3) while maintaining spatial separation >3\u03c3 between clusters. Statistical validity was ensured through Shapiro-Wilk normality tests (W >0.9 for all dimensions). The 3D scatter plot was selected to preserve geometric relationships between multivariate data points while maintaining Tufte's data-ink ratio through minimal axis framing and high-contrast markers. Cairo's principles of proportional ink and depth cues are implemented through controlled 3D rotation (\u03b1=15\u00b0, \u03b2=40\u00b0) and distinct marker symbols. Plot band on Z-axis (4-6 range) highlights the natural separation boundary between clusters, with cluster means positioned at \u00b13\u03c3 from this zone to emphasize statistical significance."
